00:10:56,560 --> 00:11:00,360
Just the reflection about the x-axis,

294
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:03,140
that's called z star.

295
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:08,440
Another way that we could represent it,

296
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:11,360
if we were using the notation of complex vector spaces,

297
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:16,300
would be that way.

298
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,180
This is called the Bra vector.

299
00:11:19,180 --> 00:11:20,240
This is called the ket vector.

300
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:21,420
When you put one next to another,

301
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:23,140
it's called a bra ket or a bracket.

302
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:27,000
Really,

303
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:30,490
the Bra vectors are really basically

304
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:33,980
just complex conjugates of the ket vectors.

305
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,930
So if we were just

306
00:11:35,930 --> 00:11:37,420
dealing with a one-dimensional vector space,

307
00:11:37,420 --> 00:11:38,580
complex vector space,

308
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,640
just the complex numbers,

309
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,680
we might easily use the notation z and z star,

310
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:45,120
or ket z and Bra z,

311
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,120
and they would mean essentially the same thing.

312
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:49,520
Okay,

313
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:52,910
let me just point out one

314
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:56,300
more important property that we will use,

315
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,840
and we'll use the analog of it for vector spaces.

316
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:03,230
The reason I'm doing this now is to do something in

317
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:06,760
a very simple context that we'll do over in more complicated contexts.

318
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:09,040
Supposing I have two complex numbers,

319
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:09,980
z1 and z2,

320
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:11,160
and I multiply them together.

321
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,700
Let's just do it over here quickly.

322
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:17,180
z1 is x1 plus Iy1.

323
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:18,680
z1 is x1 plus Iy1.

324
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:22,400
z2 is x2 plus Iy2.

325
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,440
Thank you.

326
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:30,640
We multiply these together just to do it once.

327
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:31,720
It's x1,

328
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,640
x and y are both real.

329
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:37,120
x1 times x2 is x1x2.

330
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,820
That's real.

331
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:42,840
We have also another term in

332
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:45,180
the real part that's y1 times y2,

333
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:46,360
but it has a minus sign

334
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:48,680
because i times i is minus 1,

335
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:51,300
so that's minus y1 y2.

336
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:54,700
This is the real part of the product.

337
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:57,560
And then there's the imaginary part plus i,

338
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:59,160
and what multiplies i?

339
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:03,860
i gets multiplied by x1 y2 plus y1 x2.

340
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:10,760
x1 y2 plus x2 y1.

341
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:12,700
All right.

342
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:15,360
So here we would take the product,

343
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:18,560
and separate it into a real and imaginary part,

344
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:20,610
and that defines for us the

345
00:13:20,610 --> 00:13:22,440
real and imaginary part of the product.

346
00:13:23,620 --> 00:13:25,440
A very simple theorem.

347
00:13:25,820 --> 00:13:26,720
It's a theorem.

348
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:27,560
It's hardly a theorem.

349
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,120
It's just a little exercise.

350
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:33,840
The complex conjugate of a product.

351
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,560
How do you get it?

352
00:13:35,740 --> 00:13:38,410
What you do is you just

353
00:13:38,410 --> 00:13:41,080
change each plus i to minus i.

354
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:42,760
Okay.

355
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:45,080
Each plus i becomes minus i.

356
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:49,100
That gives you the complex conjugates of z1 and z2.

357
00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:50,460
And what will it do?

358
00:13:50,740 --> 00:13:52,240
You work your way through this,

359
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:54,180
and it will just change the i over here.

360
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:54,860
Nothing else.

361
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,760
The simple Lemma theorem,

362
00:13:58,760 --> 00:13:59,860
whatever it is,

363
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:03,970
is just that the complex conjugate of

364
00:14:03,970 --> 00:14:08,040
z1 z2 is just z1 star z2 star.

365
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:10,680
In other words,

366
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,460
you multiply the complex conjugates.

367
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:17,620
Just for notational reasons,

368
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:20,060
I'm going to change the order here,

369
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,500
and put the 2 here and the 1 here.

370
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,160
Oh,

371
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:25,900
another example,

372
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:27,540
another similar fact.

373
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:33,900
What about z1 star z2?

374
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:37,020
Supposing I take z1 star z2.

375
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,200
That's a thing I can write down.

376
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:40,560
And I take its complex conjugate.

377
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:44,060
The complex conjugate of this product.

378
00:14:44,380 --> 00:14:48,040
The rule is just complex conjugate each factor.

379
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:52,360
And that's just equal to z2 times z1 star.

380
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:56,020
So when you complex conjugate a product,

381
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:59,760
you just complex conjugate...

382
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,500
Did I write it right?

383
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:02,500
No.

384
00:15:03,260 --> 00:15:03,900
Z...

385
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:05,260
That should just...

386
00:15:05,260 --> 00:15:05,340
Yeah.

387
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:06,220
Thank you.

388
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,120
Z2 star z1.

389
00:15:09,780 --> 00:15:11,960
Is there a way to write it here?

390
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,380
If you write the exponential?

391
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,240
Sure it is.

392
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,080
But I don't want to do that now.

393
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:18,120
Yeah.

394
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:23,860
Another way to write it,

395
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:24,960
to write the same thing,

396
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:28,460
which generalizes to vector spaces,

397
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:30,120
to more complicated vector spaces,

398
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:34,300
is that if I have two complex vectors,

399
00:15:35,140 --> 00:15:36,220
let's call them,

400
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,780
instead of calling them by the notation z now,

401
00:15:39,420 --> 00:15:41,720
let's just call them a and b.

402
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:45,680
All right.

403
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:46,660
The rule here is now,

404
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:49,880
think of the b's as being complex conjugates

405
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:50,940
because they're bra vectors,

406
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:53,800
and a's as being the original vector space

407
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,100
because they're ket vectors.

408
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:56,220
All right.

409
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:56,760
Well,

410
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:59,820
the rule that is analogous to this

411
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:01,760
is that if we interchange...

412
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:01,940
Here,

413
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:02,800
look at this for a moment.

414
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:07,700
Supposing we interchange z1 and z2,

415
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:09,140
what happens to the result?

416
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:15,480
If we interchange z1 and z2,

417
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:17,960
let's do it right here.

418
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,180
The interchange,

419
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,880
this is the interchange operation.

420
00:16:21,340 --> 00:16:22,920
The interchange operation

421
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:28,920
will turn this into z1 star z2.

422
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,060
Just interchanging 1 and 2.

423
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,720
Just interchanging 1 and 2

424
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:35,360
will replace z2 by z1,

425
00:16:35,420 --> 00:16:37,320
and z1 by z2.

426
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:40,000
But this is just a complex conjugate of this.

427
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:43,240
So interchanging the 1 and 2,

428
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:45,080
or the bras and the kets,

429
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:48,440
just does nothing but complex conjugates.

430
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:49,300
So,

431
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,040
to make it short,

432
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,420
if I take the...

433
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:55,620
Well,

434
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:57,260
if I take some sort of product,

435
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,500
we haven't defined this yet,

436
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:01,100
but I'm just writing it down for future reference.

437
00:17:01,780 --> 00:17:04,720
If I think of complex numbers as vectors

438
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:05,520
in a vector space,

439
00:17:05,819 --> 00:17:07,680
and I multiply the bra's and the kets,

440
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:11,180
which means multiply the complex numbers

441
00:17:11,180 --> 00:17:12,800
by their complex conjugates,

442
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:17,220
then you just interchange the two complex numbers

443
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:19,180
and complex conjugate.

444
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:24,420
So when you interchange the bras and kets,

445
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:26,480
it's equivalent to complex conjugation.

446
00:17:26,619 --> 00:17:30,700
We'll come back to it in some detail very shortly.

447
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,820
It's just a useful thing to keep in mind

448
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:36,850
that the mapping,

449
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:39,490
the mapping from bras to kets

450
00:17:39,490 --> 00:17:42,150
is essentially complex conjugation.

451
00:17:42,570 --> 00:17:43,070
Okay,

452
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:44,630
let's go back and very briefly,

453
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:47,990
quickly review what a complex vector space is.

454
00:17:49,510 --> 00:17:50,430
As I said,

455
00:17:50,430 --> 00:17:54,030
it is really the heart of the mathematics

456
00:17:54,030 --> 00:17:55,170
of quantum mechanics,

457
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:56,610
and we can't do without it,

458
00:17:56,630 --> 00:17:58,210
so we have to spend a little bit of time.

459
00:17:59,230 --> 00:18:00,170
First of all,

460
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:02,090
it has a set of elements called A.

461
00:18:03,130 --> 00:18:03,630
A,

462
00:18:03,630 --> 00:18:03,970
B,

463
00:18:03,970 --> 00:18:04,370
C,

464
00:18:04,370 --> 00:18:04,990
and so forth.

465
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:06,290
How many of them?

466
00:18:06,410 --> 00:18:08,190
An infinite number of them,

467
00:18:08,310 --> 00:18:08,810
but not,

468
00:18:08,810 --> 00:18:09,890
as we'll see,

469
00:18:10,670 --> 00:18:12,010
infinite in a certain sense.

470
00:18:13,570 --> 00:18:15,210
Just like the complex numbers,

471
00:18:15,410 --> 00:18:16,990
there are an infinite number of complex numbers,

472
00:18:17,670 --> 00:18:20,310
there's also an infinite number of elements

473
00:18:20,310 --> 00:18:21,850
that we're going to call A.

474
00:18:23,590 --> 00:18:25,250
They have the property that,

475
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:25,910
first of all,

476
00:18:25,930 --> 00:18:27,850
you can multiply any one of them

477
00:18:27,850 --> 00:18:29,550
by a complex number,

478
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:30,790
alpha,

479
00:18:31,370 --> 00:18:32,530
and you get a new one.

480
00:18:33,030 --> 00:18:33,930
Let's call it C.

481
00:18:36,530 --> 00:18:39,210
So multiplication by a complex number

482
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:41,810
is an allowed operation.

483
00:18:41,890 --> 00:18:42,970
It gives you another vector,

484
00:18:43,110 --> 00:18:45,310
and adding them,

485
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:46,730
A plus B,

486
00:18:51,129 --> 00:18:53,090
is another allowable operation.

487
00:18:53,530 --> 00:18:55,210
You can put these two together,

488
00:18:55,670 --> 00:18:56,490
and you can say,

489
00:18:56,490 --> 00:18:58,970
given any two vectors,

490
00:18:59,970 --> 00:19:01,250
any two complex vectors,

491
00:19:01,670 --> 00:19:03,990
you can add them alpha A,

492
00:19:05,010 --> 00:19:06,570
plus beta B,

493
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:14,490
and get another complex number.

494
00:19:17,670 --> 00:19:22,330
If you can multiply them by complex numbers,

495
00:19:22,670 --> 00:19:24,010
and if you can add them,

496
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:26,070
then you can add them in combination

497
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:27,990
with coefficients in front of them.

498
00:19:28,530 --> 00:19:32,250
And the point is that they're closed

499
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:33,510
under these operations.

500
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:34,750
See,

501
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:37,250
alphas and betas can be any complex numbers.

502
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:37,930
Now,

503
00:19:37,930 --> 00:19:38,530
for example,

504
00:19:38,530 --> 00:19:39,770
this would preclude

505
00:19:43,469 --> 00:19:47,410
the real numbers as being a complex vector space.

506
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:50,510
The real numbers cannot be multiplied

507
00:19:50,510 --> 00:19:53,690
by complex numbers and give back real numbers.

508
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:57,250
So the real numbers are not a complex vector space.

509
00:19:57,790 --> 00:20:00,350
They are a real vector space,

510
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:03,490
meaning to say that the real numbers can be multiplied

511
00:20:04,629 --> 00:20:06,670
by other real numbers,

512
00:20:06,670 --> 00:20:07,430
real constants,

513
00:20:07,670 --> 00:20:08,730
and they can be added.

514
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:10,730
So they're a real vector space.

515
00:20:11,530 --> 00:20:13,410
But what about the positive numbers?

516
00:20:13,550 --> 00:20:17,730
Are the positive numbers a vector space?

517
00:20:19,670 --> 00:20:21,270
Under the reals?

518
00:20:21,330 --> 00:20:21,990
No,

519
00:20:21,990 --> 00:20:24,390
because part of the definition

520
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:25,730
of a real vector space

521
00:20:25,730 --> 00:20:27,070
is that you can multiply numbers

522
00:20:27,070 --> 00:20:28,370
by any real number,

523
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:29,950
positive or negative.

524
00:20:31,690 --> 00:20:32,350
So,

525
00:20:36,450 --> 00:20:37,730
and that's it.

526
00:20:37,850 --> 00:20:40,650
That is the definition of a complex vector space.

527
00:20:41,330 --> 00:20:42,710
Let me give you two examples.

528
00:20:42,870 --> 00:20:44,030
We talked about them last time,

529
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:45,310
just to review them very quickly.

530
00:20:45,950 --> 00:20:46,910
One example,

531
00:20:49,129 --> 00:20:49,610
oh,

532
00:20:49,610 --> 00:20:52,430
ordinary vectors are vectors,

533
00:20:52,610 --> 00:20:53,890
form a vector space,

534
00:20:54,430 --> 00:20:55,820
and they form a vector space

535
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,210
which is a real vector space.

536
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:58,370
Ordinary vectors,

537
00:20:58,370 --> 00:20:59,630
which are just arrows in space,

538
00:21:00,470 --> 00:21:02,810
can be multiplied and added.

539
00:21:02,810 --> 00:21:05,030
But multiplied only by real numbers.

540
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:07,970
Does not make sense to take an ordinary vector,

541
00:21:09,410 --> 00:21:10,610
my finger,

542
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:12,890
and multiply it by a complex number.

543
00:21:13,610 --> 00:21:14,090
Alright,

544
00:21:14,090 --> 00:21:16,030
so ordinary vectors are a vector space,

545
00:21:16,190 --> 00:21:17,270
but they're a real vector space.

546
00:21:22,570 --> 00:21:22,870
Alright,

547
00:21:22,870 --> 00:21:24,690
some examples of complex vector spaces.

548
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:27,950
Complex functions,

549
00:21:30,610 --> 00:21:31,750
let's call it psi,

550
00:21:32,470 --> 00:21:35,290
a function of a variable.

551
00:21:35,790 --> 00:21:36,310
Now,

552
00:21:36,310 --> 00:21:38,590
the variable does not have to be complex.

553
00:21:38,990 --> 00:21:40,470
It can be complex,

554
00:21:40,470 --> 00:21:41,950
but it doesn't have to be complex.

555
00:21:42,410 --> 00:21:44,710
It could just be an

556
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:47,010
ordinary real argument of a function.

557
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:49,270
Argument means the thing that the function depends on.

558
00:21:49,670 --> 00:21:50,970
Psi of x,

559
00:21:51,830 --> 00:21:53,150
where x is real,

560
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:55,550
but psi is complex.

561
00:21:56,230 --> 00:21:57,270
In other words,

562
00:21:57,270 --> 00:21:58,710
psi is of the form,

563
00:21:58,830 --> 00:22:00,290
some real part,

564
00:22:00,570 --> 00:22:02,110
let's call it psi real of x,

565
00:22:02,950 --> 00:22:06,250
plus i times psi imaginary of x.

566
00:22:08,110 --> 00:22:10,270
That's the collection of complex

567
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:12,430
functions of a real variable,

568
00:22:12,550 --> 00:22:13,070
for example.

569
00:22:13,890 --> 00:22:14,450
Okay?

570
00:22:14,590 --> 00:22:16,170
These form a vector space,

571
00:22:16,510 --> 00:22:17,110
y,

572
00:22:17,330 --> 00:22:19,650
you can multiply them by numbers,

573
00:22:19,670 --> 00:22:20,970
and you get new functions.

574
00:22:21,230 --> 00:22:22,890
You can multiply them by complex numbers.

575
00:22:23,210 --> 00:22:25,370
If I take a complex function,

576
00:22:25,550 --> 00:22:26,250
psi of x,

577
00:22:26,250 --> 00:22:28,830
and multiply it by any complex number,

578
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:30,330
say alpha,

579
00:22:32,889 --> 00:22:34,870
I get a new complex function.

580
00:22:35,770 --> 00:22:36,510
Number one.

581
00:22:36,670 --> 00:22:37,410
Number two,

582
00:22:37,410 --> 00:22:39,170
I can add complex functions.

583
00:22:39,550 --> 00:22:40,310
Two psi,

584
00:22:40,310 --> 00:22:41,550
a psi and a phi,

585
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:42,210
for example.

586
00:22:42,730 --> 00:22:44,670
Psi of x plus phi of x

587
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:46,810
gives me another complex function.

588
00:22:47,770 --> 00:22:48,250
So,

589
00:22:48,250 --> 00:22:50,130
they form a complex vector space.

590
00:22:50,310 --> 00:22:50,410
Now,

591
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:51,290
we're not used to thinking,

592
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:51,570
I mean,

593
00:22:51,570 --> 00:22:53,330
unless you've been doing this for some time,

594
00:22:53,490 --> 00:22:55,410
you may not be used to thinking of functions,

595
00:22:55,410 --> 00:22:56,810
as vectors.

596
00:22:57,210 --> 00:22:59,830
But they are vectors in this mathematical sense.

597
00:23:00,770 --> 00:23:01,370
Okay?

598
00:23:01,610 --> 00:23:03,950
Another example that we'll use over and over,

599
00:23:04,070 --> 00:23:05,450
are column vectors.

600
00:23:06,530 --> 00:23:09,170
Column vectors are really functions also.

601
00:23:09,610 --> 00:23:11,910
They're functions of a discrete index.

602
00:23:12,410 --> 00:23:13,810
A discrete index,

603
00:23:13,810 --> 00:23:15,570
instead of a continuous x,

604
00:23:15,910 --> 00:23:17,050
they're functions,

605
00:23:17,050 --> 00:23:18,370
perhaps of an integer,

606
00:23:18,590 --> 00:23:19,660
but maybe an integer that

607
00:23:19,660 --> 00:23:20,730
only goes from one to four,

608
00:23:20,870 --> 00:23:21,590
or one to three,

609
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:22,450
or one to seven.

610
00:23:23,370 --> 00:23:23,970
Uh,

611
00:23:23,970 --> 00:23:30,710
and we can represent them by a column.

612
00:23:31,790 --> 00:23:34,690
I'm going to use for these discrete kind of vectors,

613
00:23:34,950 --> 00:23:40,070
I'm going to use a's and little b's,

614
00:23:40,110 --> 00:23:41,270
little a's and little b's.

615
00:23:41,530 --> 00:23:43,990
But if I put the entries into the column,

616
00:23:45,490 --> 00:23:46,010
a1,

617
00:23:46,010 --> 00:23:46,530
a2,

618
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:47,830
a3,

619
00:23:47,890 --> 00:23:48,930
these are just numbers now,

620
00:23:48,930 --> 00:23:49,830
complex numbers.

621
00:23:50,990 --> 00:23:51,510
A4,

622
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:52,170
for example.

623
00:23:53,970 --> 00:23:56,930
The set of column objects like this,

624
00:23:56,990 --> 00:23:58,710
with only four complex entries,

625
00:23:59,070 --> 00:24:00,670
forms a vector space.

626
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:02,930
You can add two of them,

627
00:24:03,010 --> 00:24:04,590
by the following operation.

628
00:24:04,950 --> 00:24:06,170
Let's call it b1,

629
00:24:06,170 --> 00:24:07,010
b2,

630
00:24:07,010 --> 00:24:08,210
dot dot.

631
00:24:10,090 --> 00:24:10,990
And define,

632
00:24:10,990 --> 00:24:12,670
this is definition of adding them.

633
00:24:14,730 --> 00:24:16,290
a1 plus b1,

634
00:24:16,290 --> 00:24:18,170
a2 plus b2,

635
00:24:18,410 --> 00:24:20,250
a3 plus b3,

636
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:22,630
a4 plus b4,

637
00:24:23,970 --> 00:24:25,050
and so on.

638
00:24:26,250 --> 00:24:28,650
You can also multiply them by constants.

639
00:24:29,050 --> 00:24:31,910
If I want to multiply the vector a,

640
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:33,170
by a constant,

641
00:24:33,390 --> 00:24:35,390
let's call that constant alpha again,

642
00:24:36,669 --> 00:24:39,610
all I do is multiply the entries by alpha.

643
00:24:39,910 --> 00:24:42,190
Each entry gets multiplied by alpha.

644
00:24:43,230 --> 00:24:44,710
And so alpha,

645
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:49,130
times a column vector,

646
00:24:49,810 --> 00:24:51,810
is just a column vector by definition,

647
00:24:52,130 --> 00:24:53,230
which is,

648
00:24:53,230 --> 00:24:55,150
alpha a1,

649
00:24:55,150 --> 00:24:57,170
alpha a2,

650
00:24:57,170 --> 00:24:58,450
dot dot dot.

651
00:24:59,450 --> 00:25:01,290
So you can multiply them by constants.

652
00:25:01,650 --> 00:25:03,070
It's kind of obvious,

653
00:25:04,550 --> 00:25:06,670
that this notation here,

654
00:25:08,550 --> 00:25:11,290
is describing components of a vector.

655
00:25:11,670 --> 00:25:12,950
We could in fact,

656
00:25:13,190 --> 00:25:15,450
think of these entries here,

657
00:25:15,710 --> 00:25:18,190
as kind of like the components of a vector.

658
00:25:18,390 --> 00:25:19,710
If I were to give

659
00:25:19,710 --> 00:25:21,030
you an ordinary vector in space,

660
00:25:21,970 --> 00:25:23,210
let's say three dimensional,

661
00:25:23,210 --> 00:25:23,630
three dimensional space,

662
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:27,710
I could describe that vector,

663
00:25:27,850 --> 00:25:29,290
by three components,

664
00:25:29,490 --> 00:25:29,670
x,

665
00:25:29,670 --> 00:25:29,950
y,

666
00:25:29,950 --> 00:25:30,290
and z.

667
00:25:31,290 --> 00:25:32,410
And if I liked,

668
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:34,670
if I wanted to,

669
00:25:34,870 --> 00:25:37,030
I could exhibit those components,

670
00:25:37,050 --> 00:25:37,950
in the form x,

671
00:25:37,950 --> 00:25:38,170
y,

672
00:25:38,170 --> 00:25:38,510
and z.

673
00:25:40,170 --> 00:25:41,650
But of course now I would

674
00:25:41,650 --> 00:25:43,130
be talking about a real vector space,

675
00:25:43,690 --> 00:25:44,410
and the x,

676
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:47,110
y's and z's would be real.

677
00:25:48,390 --> 00:25:50,850
So there's nothing terribly unusual,

678
00:25:51,090 --> 00:25:52,110
about what I'm doing here.

679
00:25:53,210 --> 00:25:54,830
You can also think of these objects,

680
00:25:55,310 --> 00:25:57,110
as functions of the index.

681
00:25:58,190 --> 00:25:59,670
If I tell you which index,

682
00:25:59,910 --> 00:26:01,550
if I tell you I'm talking about three,

683
00:26:01,850 --> 00:26:03,050
then a of three,

684
00:26:03,790 --> 00:26:04,950
would be a function,

685
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:05,490
well,

686
00:26:05,490 --> 00:26:06,150
it would be a,

687
00:26:07,370 --> 00:26:09,990
it would be a function of a discrete variable,

688
00:26:10,150 --> 00:26:11,630
which goes from one to four here.

689
00:26:12,390 --> 00:26:13,970
So in that sense,

690
00:26:15,470 --> 00:26:16,970
even these discrete vectors,

691
00:26:17,090 --> 00:26:18,450
can be thought of as functions.

692
00:26:18,630 --> 00:26:19,890
Not continuous functions,

693
00:26:20,050 --> 00:26:21,390
but just functions with,

694
00:26:21,390 --> 00:26:25,290
whose independent variable just takes on four values,

695
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:25,670
one,

696
00:26:25,670 --> 00:26:25,950
two,

697
00:26:25,950 --> 00:26:26,190
three,

698
00:26:26,190 --> 00:26:26,510
and four.

699
00:26:28,990 --> 00:26:29,510
Okay.

700
00:26:30,970 --> 00:26:31,490
Now,

701
00:26:31,490 --> 00:26:33,490
what about the dimension of a vector space?

702
00:26:34,210 --> 00:26:36,010
The dimension of a vector space,

703
00:26:37,010 --> 00:26:38,110
can be defined,

704
00:26:39,910 --> 00:26:40,790
as follows.

705
00:26:52,050 --> 00:26:53,570
You can define it,

706
00:26:53,610 --> 00:26:54,690
as the,

707
00:26:55,629 --> 00:26:57,510
minimum number of vectors,

708
00:26:57,910 --> 00:26:59,450
that you need,

709
00:26:59,690 --> 00:27:01,990
so that you can write any vector,

710
00:27:03,710 --> 00:27:05,210
as a sum,

711
00:27:05,550 --> 00:27:06,990
with coefficients,

712
00:27:07,450 --> 00:27:08,950
of that minimum number.

713
00:27:09,570 --> 00:27:11,430
Let me give you an example.

714
00:27:11,850 --> 00:27:14,290
Let's take a one dimensional vector space,

715
00:27:14,770 --> 00:27:16,910
just the ordinary line.

716
00:27:17,910 --> 00:27:18,630
Okay.

717
00:27:18,750 --> 00:27:20,770
Now we can think of vectors on the line.

718
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:22,590
Vectors on the line,

719
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:24,310
are just of course real numbers,

720
00:27:24,630 --> 00:27:26,130
but I can represent them,

721
00:27:26,210 --> 00:27:27,050
as arrows,

722
00:27:27,590 --> 00:27:28,950
from zero to,

723
00:27:29,090 --> 00:27:30,890
to some real number.

724
00:27:32,650 --> 00:27:33,770
If I'm allowed,

725
00:27:33,990 --> 00:27:34,850
to multiply,

726
00:27:35,010 --> 00:27:36,250
this vector,

727
00:27:36,450 --> 00:27:37,910
this could be a unit vector,

728
00:27:38,050 --> 00:27:39,310
or it doesn't have to be a unit vector,

729
00:27:39,830 --> 00:27:40,310
but,

730
00:27:40,370 --> 00:27:42,570
if I'm allowed to multiply this vector,

731
00:27:42,650 --> 00:27:44,110
by any real number,

732
00:27:44,270 --> 00:27:45,090
let's call it r,

733
00:27:45,390 --> 00:27:47,090
and let's call this the vector v,

734
00:27:51,830 --> 00:27:52,770
then I can,

735
00:27:52,830 --> 00:27:54,850
and r can be positive or negative,

736
00:27:55,370 --> 00:27:57,650
then I can get any vector out of it.

737
00:27:57,810 --> 00:27:59,630
So it only takes one vector,

738
00:28:01,110 --> 00:28:02,170
to get started,

739
00:28:02,290 --> 00:28:04,570
and to be able to represent any vector,

740
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:05,530
by,

741
00:28:06,650 --> 00:28:07,530
in this case,

742
00:28:07,570 --> 00:28:09,110
just multiplying it by a constant.

743
00:28:09,650 --> 00:28:11,810
Now let's go to a two dimensional vector space.

744
00:28:12,010 --> 00:28:13,210
A two dimensional vector space,

745
00:28:13,470 --> 00:28:15,090
and I'm thinking now about real vectors,

746
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:15,610
just to,

747
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:17,170
just so we can draw it on the blackboard.

748
00:28:17,430 --> 00:28:19,690
The blackboard is a two dimensional vector space.

749
00:28:20,330 --> 00:28:22,930
If I give you any two vectors,

750
00:28:23,030 --> 00:28:25,370
which happen not to lie on the same line,

751
00:28:28,190 --> 00:28:30,350
if I give you any two vectors,

752
00:28:30,450 --> 00:28:33,010
which happen not to lie on the same line,

753
00:28:33,230 --> 00:28:35,990
then by multiplying this vector,

754
00:28:36,090 --> 00:28:37,070
let's call this v1,

755
00:28:37,290 --> 00:28:38,510
let's call this v2,

756
00:28:40,670 --> 00:28:43,850
by multiplying v1 by a constant,

757
00:28:45,130 --> 00:28:45,650
r1,

758
00:28:45,650 --> 00:28:46,510
let's say,

759
00:28:46,570 --> 00:28:47,410
times v1,

760
00:28:48,290 --> 00:28:49,330
plus r2,

761
00:28:49,690 --> 00:28:50,430
times v2,

762
00:28:51,110 --> 00:28:53,670
I can generate any vector in the plane.

763
00:28:54,490 --> 00:28:56,290
All I need is two vectors.

764
00:28:57,770 --> 00:29:00,410
I could draw another vector in here,

765
00:29:02,390 --> 00:29:02,950
v3,

766
00:29:03,210 --> 00:29:04,910
but I don't need it,

767
00:29:05,850 --> 00:29:08,860
in order to represent any vector by

768
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:11,870
summing up multiples of v1 and v2.

769
00:29:12,130 --> 00:29:13,170
I don't need it,

770
00:29:13,170 --> 00:29:13,650
it's redundant.

771
00:29:14,050 --> 00:29:14,630
In fact,

772
00:29:14,630 --> 00:29:15,370
v3 itself,

773
00:29:15,630 --> 00:29:18,730
can be expressed in terms of v1 and v2.

774
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:21,870
v1 and v2 can be added

775
00:29:21,870 --> 00:29:23,910
with appropriate coefficients to get v3.

776
00:29:25,250 --> 00:29:25,850
So,

777
00:29:25,850 --> 00:29:26,990
the question is,

778
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:28,610
how many vectors do you need?

779
00:29:29,690 --> 00:29:32,230
What's the minimum number of vectors that you need

780
00:29:32,230 --> 00:29:33,790
in order to be able

781
00:29:33,790 --> 00:29:35,350
to add them up with coefficients

782
00:29:35,350 --> 00:29:38,070
and generate any vector in the vector space?

783
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:41,610
That minimum number is the dimensionality of the space.

784
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:43,090
In this case,

785
00:29:43,090 --> 00:29:43,450
it's two.

786
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:45,910
If you had a three dimensional vector space,

787
00:29:46,870 --> 00:29:47,870
for example,

788
00:29:47,870 --> 00:29:51,550
you could generate any vector by taking three vectors along

789
00:29:52,430 --> 00:29:54,650
the mutually perpendicular axes,

790
00:29:55,230 --> 00:29:57,130
or any other three vectors as long

791
00:29:57,130 --> 00:29:59,030
as they don't lie in a plane.

792
00:29:59,370 --> 00:30:01,470
As long as they don't lie in a plane.

793
00:30:01,850 --> 00:30:03,570
So it takes three vectors,

794
00:30:03,850 --> 00:30:05,970
a minimum of three vectors,

795
00:30:06,090 --> 00:30:08,370
in order to be able to represent any vector

796
00:30:08,370 --> 00:30:10,730
lying in a three dimensional vector space.

797
00:30:11,170 --> 00:30:12,710
And that's the general definition.

798
00:30:12,990 --> 00:30:14,250
How many vectors do you need

799
00:30:16,010 --> 00:30:17,400
in order to be able

800
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:18,790
to add them up with coefficients

801
00:30:18,790 --> 00:30:21,290
and represent any vector in the space?

802
00:30:22,770 --> 00:30:24,090
Let's look at some examples.

803
00:30:24,290 --> 00:30:26,250
How many vectors do you need?

804
00:30:27,550 --> 00:30:28,290
Let's take,

805
00:30:28,290 --> 00:30:29,910
here we have vectors,

806
00:30:30,030 --> 00:30:32,210
column vectors made with four entries.

807
00:30:32,630 --> 00:30:33,890
Only four entries.

808
00:30:34,330 --> 00:30:37,190
I assert that that's a four dimensional vector space.

809
00:30:37,690 --> 00:30:38,850
How do I see that?

810
00:30:39,350 --> 00:30:39,910
Well,

811
00:30:41,410 --> 00:30:43,030
there are four vectors

812
00:30:44,250 --> 00:30:45,950
and you need all of them incidentally.

813
00:30:46,350 --> 00:30:47,840
Any fewer than this you wouldn't

814
00:30:47,840 --> 00:30:49,330
be able to represent any vector.

815
00:30:49,670 --> 00:30:51,770
But you can take the four vectors to be

816
00:30:54,570 --> 00:30:55,050
comma,

817
00:31:05,370 --> 00:31:07,750
and of course the last one is

818
00:31:11,550 --> 00:31:13,430
If you add up these vectors

819
00:31:13,430 --> 00:31:14,950
with coefficients

820
00:31:16,110 --> 00:31:16,550
a1

821
00:31:20,330 --> 00:31:21,210
plus a2

822
00:31:22,610 --> 00:31:23,490
plus a3

823
00:31:24,669 --> 00:31:25,550
plus a4

824
00:31:26,110 --> 00:31:27,190
then what do you get?

825
00:31:27,630 --> 00:31:29,430
You just get the vector a1,

826
00:31:29,430 --> 00:31:29,950
a2,

827
00:31:29,950 --> 00:31:30,470
a3,

828
00:31:30,470 --> 00:31:30,850
a4.

829
00:31:31,950 --> 00:31:34,190
The first one will give you the vector a1,

830
00:31:34,190 --> 00:31:34,390
0,

831
00:31:34,390 --> 00:31:34,690
0,

832
00:31:34,690 --> 00:31:34,890
0.

833
00:31:35,070 --> 00:31:36,710
The next one will give you the vector 0,

834
00:31:36,710 --> 00:31:37,370
a2,

835
00:31:37,370 --> 00:31:38,190
and so forth.

836
00:31:38,290 --> 00:31:39,190
And when you add them up

837
00:31:39,669 --> 00:31:41,550
you'll get back to this vector.

838
00:31:41,550 --> 00:31:43,490
So the conclusion is

839
00:31:43,490 --> 00:31:44,770
that you need,

840
00:31:44,930 --> 00:31:45,690
oh incidentally,

841
00:31:45,710 --> 00:31:47,230
if you threw away one of these vectors

842
00:31:47,230 --> 00:31:50,310
then you would never be able to construct vectors,

843
00:31:50,830 --> 00:31:52,080
there would be vectors that

844
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:53,330
you couldn't construct in this way.

845
00:31:53,690 --> 00:31:54,090
Okay?

846
00:31:55,169 --> 00:31:55,970
In particular,

847
00:31:55,970 --> 00:31:57,690
let's suppose we threw this one away over here.

848
00:31:58,590 --> 00:32:00,560
Then we'd never be able to get a

849
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:02,530
vector which had something in the bottom entry here.

850
00:32:02,950 --> 00:32:04,430
So you need all four of them,

851
00:32:04,590 --> 00:32:06,030
but that's all you need.

852
00:32:06,250 --> 00:32:08,780
You don't need a fifth vector in order to be able

853
00:32:08,780 --> 00:32:11,310
to write down every vector as a sum in this way.

854
00:32:11,550 --> 00:32:12,250
So,

855
00:32:12,250 --> 00:32:13,530
a vector,

856
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:16,000
a column vector space composed

857
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:18,470
of four entries is four dimensional.

858
00:32:19,690 --> 00:32:20,690
And so on.

859
00:32:20,890 --> 00:32:23,110
Five entries would be five dimensional,

860
00:32:23,310 --> 00:32:25,030
two entries would be two dimensional.

861
00:32:25,170 --> 00:32:26,530
What about just one entry?

862
00:32:26,930 --> 00:32:30,250
One entry would be just the good old complex numbers.

863
00:32:30,310 --> 00:32:32,210
It would be a one dimensional vector space.

864
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:35,220
So a column vector with just

865
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:37,370
one entry is just a number.

866
00:32:37,490 --> 00:32:38,550
It's just a complex number.

867
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:40,410
And they form

868
00:32:40,410 --> 00:32:42,630
the one dimensional vector space.

869
00:32:42,930 --> 00:32:44,210
Complex vector space.

870
00:32:46,730 --> 00:32:47,330
Alright,

871
00:32:47,330 --> 00:32:52,570
so let's just summarize that by saying

872
00:32:57,170 --> 00:32:57,770
Oh,

873
00:32:57,770 --> 00:32:59,110
what about the functions?

874
00:32:59,670 --> 00:33:00,890
What about the functions,

875
00:33:00,890 --> 00:33:04,290
let's say the continuous smooth functions on a line.

876
00:33:05,390 --> 00:33:07,720
How many functions does it take

877
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:10,050
to be able to write every function?

878
00:33:10,410 --> 00:33:10,930
As a sum.

879
00:33:13,670 --> 00:33:14,970
An infinite number.

880
00:33:15,290 --> 00:33:16,710
Obviously an infinite number.

881
00:33:17,070 --> 00:33:19,410
There's no finite set of functions

882
00:33:19,410 --> 00:33:21,530
that you can add up with

883
00:33:21,530 --> 00:33:23,650
coefficients that will generate every function.

884
00:33:24,690 --> 00:33:26,110
If I have a few functions,

885
00:33:26,110 --> 00:33:26,730
that one,

886
00:33:26,950 --> 00:33:27,950
this one,

887
00:33:28,190 --> 00:33:29,610
a couple of others,

888
00:33:30,230 --> 00:33:32,200
it's rather limited what I can

889
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:34,170
generate by adding them up with coefficients.

890
00:33:34,710 --> 00:33:35,630
In particular,

891
00:33:35,630 --> 00:33:37,710
I'll never generate a function which looks like this.

892
00:33:39,630 --> 00:33:44,050
So you need an infinite number of functions

893
00:33:44,590 --> 00:33:48,670
in order to be able to write all functions.

894
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:50,790
Now all functions is a huge number of things.

895
00:33:50,850 --> 00:33:51,710
All continuous,

896
00:33:51,710 --> 00:33:53,050
differentiable,

897
00:33:53,050 --> 00:33:53,870
smooth functions.

898
00:33:54,110 --> 00:33:55,810
You still need an infinite number of them.

899
00:33:56,290 --> 00:33:57,530
I won't try to tell

900
00:33:57,530 --> 00:33:58,770
you how big that infinity is,

901
00:33:58,950 --> 00:34:00,490
but you need an infinite number.

902
00:34:00,770 --> 00:34:02,170
And so for that reason,

903
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:04,930
the functions are called

904
00:34:04,930 --> 00:34:07,070
an infinite dimensional vector space.

905
00:34:08,870 --> 00:34:10,090
But you can think of

906
00:34:10,090 --> 00:34:11,310
it simply as a vector space

907
00:34:11,310 --> 00:34:12,830
with an infinite number of axes.

908
00:34:13,870 --> 00:34:15,230
It's a little mind-boggling.

909
00:34:15,429 --> 00:34:16,529
I suggest you don't try

910
00:34:16,529 --> 00:34:17,630
to think about it that way.

911
00:34:19,429 --> 00:34:19,870
Okay,

912
00:34:19,870 --> 00:34:20,550
so there we are.

913
00:34:21,389 --> 00:34:23,110
We have functions.

914
00:34:34,409 --> 00:34:35,350
Psi of x.

915
00:34:35,350 --> 00:34:37,530
And we can think of them,

916
00:34:37,550 --> 00:34:39,370
this symbol means think of them as.

917
00:34:39,870 --> 00:34:42,610
We can think of them as vectors

918
00:34:44,050 --> 00:34:45,969
in a complex vector space.

919
00:34:47,150 --> 00:34:52,110
Psi of x is another vector.

920
00:34:52,330 --> 00:34:53,550
These are two different vectors.

921
00:34:53,730 --> 00:34:56,090
And they form an infinite dimensional vector space.

922
00:34:56,590 --> 00:34:57,750
In the same way,

923
00:34:57,750 --> 00:34:59,270
the column vectors,

924
00:35:00,290 --> 00:35:01,770
a one dot dot,

925
00:35:01,770 --> 00:35:02,010
a,

926
00:35:02,010 --> 00:35:04,450
let's say six this time,

927
00:35:04,450 --> 00:35:05,770
a six dimensional vector space,

928
00:35:06,410 --> 00:35:11,990
can be thought of as the vector a.

929
00:35:12,210 --> 00:35:15,570
The vector a which is determined

930
00:35:15,570 --> 00:35:18,930
by the six small letters a,

931
00:35:19,110 --> 00:35:20,150
a one through a six.

932
00:35:21,090 --> 00:35:21,690
All right,

933
00:35:21,690 --> 00:35:24,210
so that's the notation that we'll use

934
00:35:25,610 --> 00:35:27,070
to describe vectors.

935
00:35:28,590 --> 00:35:29,710
And typically,

936
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:32,210
vectors are closely related to functions,

937
00:35:32,450 --> 00:35:34,310
either of continuous,

938
00:35:34,450 --> 00:35:36,150
or discrete variables.

939
00:35:42,330 --> 00:35:44,470
Now we come to the

940
00:35:44,470 --> 00:35:46,610
idea of the dual vector space.

941
00:35:46,990 --> 00:35:49,890
The dual vector space is really just

942
00:35:49,890 --> 00:35:52,050
the complex conjugate vector space.

943
00:35:53,890 --> 00:35:57,490
That's a secret that mathematicians don't let out.

944
00:35:58,190 --> 00:35:58,890
Well,

945
00:35:58,890 --> 00:36:01,270
for good reasons.

946
00:36:01,370 --> 00:36:02,250
It's not arbitrary.

947
00:36:02,930 --> 00:36:04,430
When they want to be general,

948
00:36:04,450 --> 00:36:05,530
and they want to be rigorous,

949
00:36:06,210 --> 00:36:09,730
they prefer not to think of the dual vector space

950
00:36:10,370 --> 00:36:13,830
as being limited to just complex conjugation.

951
00:36:13,870 --> 00:36:15,610
You can have other kinds of operations.

952
00:36:15,990 --> 00:36:18,190
But for us in physics and in quantum mechanics,

953
00:36:18,430 --> 00:36:20,540
basically the dual vector

954
00:36:20,540 --> 00:36:22,650
space means the complex conjugates.

955
00:36:25,950 --> 00:36:28,250
And we think of the complex conjugates

956
00:36:28,250 --> 00:36:31,690
as forming a separate vector space,

957
00:36:31,690 --> 00:36:32,570
a different one,

958
00:36:32,570 --> 00:36:33,410
but related.

959
00:36:35,130 --> 00:36:35,750
So,

960
00:36:35,750 --> 00:36:38,450
just like for every complex number,

961
00:36:40,450 --> 00:36:42,170
we have its reflection.

962
00:36:42,690 --> 00:36:45,690
If the complex number is in the upper half plane,

963
00:36:46,030 --> 00:36:48,590
then its reflection is in the lower half plane.

964
00:36:48,870 --> 00:36:51,350
If the complex number is in the lower half plane,

965
00:36:51,650 --> 00:36:54,010
then its reflection is in the upper half plane.

966
00:36:54,310 --> 00:36:55,770
We actually have two,

967
00:36:55,890 --> 00:36:59,010
a pair of redundant descriptions of the same plane.

968
00:36:59,010 --> 00:37:01,690
One in terms of the complex numbers,

969
00:37:01,990 --> 00:37:05,130
and the other in terms of the complex conjugates.

970
00:37:06,470 --> 00:37:07,970
It's really the same plane,

971
00:37:08,250 --> 00:37:12,630
but we think of them as two different vector spaces.

972
00:37:13,850 --> 00:37:16,250
But there's a mapping between them.

973
00:37:16,630 --> 00:37:18,090
For every complex number,

974
00:37:18,330 --> 00:37:19,930
there is a complex conjugate.

975
00:37:20,750 --> 00:37:24,510
For every ket vector z,

976
00:37:24,770 --> 00:37:26,530
there is a bra vector z.

977
00:37:26,730 --> 00:37:27,890
It's complex conjugate.

978
00:37:27,890 --> 00:37:31,850
And so we think of a vector space

979
00:37:31,850 --> 00:37:34,810
coming together with a second vector space,

980
00:37:35,150 --> 00:37:35,550
which is,

981
00:37:35,550 --> 00:37:36,630
in a certain sense,

982
00:37:36,630 --> 00:37:37,730
identical to it,

983
00:37:37,790 --> 00:37:40,370
or isomorphic to it,

984
00:37:41,710 --> 00:37:43,330
contains the same...

985
00:37:44,990 --> 00:37:45,510
Well,

986
00:37:45,510 --> 00:37:46,970
I won't say it contains the same object.

987
00:37:47,150 --> 00:37:48,910
That would be wrong.

988
00:37:49,370 --> 00:37:52,390
But they're in one-to-one correspondence.

989
00:37:52,850 --> 00:37:54,030
They're in one-to-one correspondence.

990
00:37:55,130 --> 00:37:57,030
But let's suppose now

991
00:37:58,750 --> 00:37:59,310
that the vector space is a vector space.

992
00:37:59,310 --> 00:38:00,290
And they're labeled,

993
00:38:01,430 --> 00:38:05,150
if A is a vector in the ket space,

994
00:38:06,030 --> 00:38:06,950
then A,

995
00:38:09,290 --> 00:38:11,810
with its arrow facing in the other direction,

996
00:38:12,050 --> 00:38:14,530
is essentially its complex conjugate.

997
00:38:14,990 --> 00:38:16,070
What does that mean?

998
00:38:16,350 --> 00:38:16,910
Well,

999
00:38:16,910 --> 00:38:17,950
for example,

1000
00:38:17,950 --> 00:38:19,950
if the vector space is the space of functions,

1001
00:38:21,290 --> 00:38:23,410
then the dual vector space is simply

1002
00:38:23,410 --> 00:38:25,990
the things made up out of the complex conjugates

1003
00:38:25,990 --> 00:38:26,550
of the functions.

1004
00:38:27,890 --> 00:38:29,090
There's a mapping between them.

1005
00:38:29,150 --> 00:38:29,950
For every A,

1006
00:38:31,990 --> 00:38:32,790
there is...

1007
00:38:32,790 --> 00:38:34,690
For every ket vector,

1008
00:38:34,950 --> 00:38:36,250
there is a bra vector.

1009
00:38:37,609 --> 00:38:39,370
Just as for every complex number,

1010
00:38:39,710 --> 00:38:41,930
there is its complex conjugate.

1011
00:38:42,589 --> 00:38:44,010
So one example of this

1012
00:38:44,589 --> 00:38:46,430
is the mapping of...

1013
00:38:47,710 --> 00:38:49,690
between complex conjugates.

1014
00:38:52,050 --> 00:38:54,590
It's always a mapping between complex conjugates.

1015
00:38:54,890 --> 00:38:57,670
But if we were talking about column vectors,

1016
00:39:00,009 --> 00:39:02,070
then the usual notation...

1017
00:39:02,070 --> 00:39:02,190
Now,

1018
00:39:02,190 --> 00:39:03,370
some of these things are just notations.

1019
00:39:03,430 --> 00:39:04,390
You can't ask me why,

1020
00:39:05,750 --> 00:39:07,030
because it's just a notation.

1021
00:39:07,310 --> 00:39:08,430
It turns out to be convenient.

1022
00:39:09,070 --> 00:39:12,490
If you represent the original ket vectors

1023
00:39:13,130 --> 00:39:14,150
by a column,

1024
00:39:16,090 --> 00:39:17,190
then the bra vectors

1025
00:39:17,190 --> 00:39:19,310
are represented by a row.

1026
00:39:19,810 --> 00:39:21,230
It's nice to keep track

1027
00:39:21,230 --> 00:39:23,550
of which are the bras and which are the kets

1028
00:39:23,550 --> 00:39:26,370
by making the kets be columns

1029
00:39:26,370 --> 00:39:28,970
and the bras be rows.

1030
00:39:29,370 --> 00:39:30,990
But the entry to the rows

1031
00:39:30,990 --> 00:39:32,990
are the complex conjugate numbers.

1032
00:39:33,750 --> 00:39:35,310
That's the important thing.

1033
00:39:42,250 --> 00:39:43,030
All right,

1034
00:39:43,030 --> 00:39:44,950
so for every column vector,

1035
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:47,730
you have the complex conjugate row vector,

1036
00:39:48,430 --> 00:39:50,650
and those form the bras and the kets.

1037
00:39:50,690 --> 00:39:53,850
This can be thought of as

1038
00:39:54,370 --> 00:39:55,370
the bra vector,

1039
00:39:55,370 --> 00:39:56,970
this can be thought of

1040
00:39:56,970 --> 00:39:58,910
as the ket vector.

1041
00:39:59,930 --> 00:40:01,890
Notice we don't put a star in here.

1042
00:40:02,090 --> 00:40:05,170
The star is indicated simply by

1043
00:40:05,170 --> 00:40:07,650
drawing the ket vector instead of the original vector.

1044
00:40:07,950 --> 00:40:10,290
So think of ket as being a symbol

1045
00:40:10,290 --> 00:40:12,230
for complex conjugation.

1046
00:40:15,190 --> 00:40:16,030
All right,

1047
00:40:16,030 --> 00:40:16,250
now,

1048
00:40:16,910 --> 00:40:18,390
supposing we have

1049
00:40:21,150 --> 00:40:22,050
two vectors...

1050
00:40:22,050 --> 00:40:23,750
not two vectors...

1051
00:40:23,750 --> 00:40:25,010
we have a vector a

1052
00:40:25,529 --> 00:40:28,910
and its image in the dual vector space.

1053
00:40:29,470 --> 00:40:30,930
We have a vector a,

1054
00:40:31,090 --> 00:40:31,910
its bra...

1055
00:40:31,910 --> 00:40:32,170
no,

1056
00:40:32,170 --> 00:40:32,550
its ket,

1057
00:40:32,710 --> 00:40:34,970
and we have its image in the dual space,

1058
00:40:35,330 --> 00:40:36,490
which is the bra.

1059
00:40:36,750 --> 00:40:39,650
Now supposing we multiply a

1060
00:40:40,890 --> 00:40:43,550
by the complex number alpha.

1061
00:40:45,730 --> 00:40:47,890
What is the image of that?

1062
00:40:49,490 --> 00:40:50,410
You might think

1063
00:40:52,410 --> 00:40:54,190
that it's just alpha

1064
00:40:55,470 --> 00:40:56,430
times a.

1065
00:40:57,250 --> 00:40:58,070
What's wrong with that?

1066
00:41:01,030 --> 00:41:02,610
You want to conjugate it.

1067
00:41:03,109 --> 00:41:05,030
Because you want the

1068
00:41:06,610 --> 00:41:09,630
bra vector associated with alpha a

1069
00:41:09,630 --> 00:41:12,210
to be the complex conjugate

1070
00:41:12,210 --> 00:41:13,890
of the ket vector,

1071
00:41:14,070 --> 00:41:15,170
and that entails

1072
00:41:16,090 --> 00:41:18,250
complex conjugating the number

1073
00:41:18,250 --> 00:41:19,790
that you multiply a by.

1074
00:41:20,410 --> 00:41:22,190
So you really want to put a star here.

1075
00:41:23,250 --> 00:41:24,170
Alpha star.

1076
00:41:25,270 --> 00:41:26,470
Complex conjugating...

1077
00:41:26,470 --> 00:41:27,390
this is just a statement

1078
00:41:27,390 --> 00:41:29,990
that complex conjugating a product

1079
00:41:31,450 --> 00:41:33,510
requires you to complex conjugate

1080
00:41:33,510 --> 00:41:35,490
both pieces of the product.

1081
00:41:36,030 --> 00:41:36,170
Okay?

1082
00:41:36,290 --> 00:41:37,290
We had...

1083
00:41:37,290 --> 00:41:37,890
where was it?

1084
00:41:37,970 --> 00:41:38,130
Yes,

1085
00:41:38,130 --> 00:41:38,930
here it is right here.

1086
00:41:39,270 --> 00:41:41,150
Complex conjugating a product

1087
00:41:41,850 --> 00:41:42,450
means

1088
00:41:44,190 --> 00:41:46,230
complex conjugating both factors.

1089
00:41:46,630 --> 00:41:49,810
So the complex conjugate of alpha times a,

1090
00:41:49,810 --> 00:41:51,430
if a was just a number for example,

1091
00:41:51,710 --> 00:41:53,790
would be the complex conjugate of a

1092
00:41:53,790 --> 00:41:55,710
times the complex conjugate of alpha.

1093
00:41:55,910 --> 00:41:58,270
Notice that when I'm speaking about simple numbers,

1094
00:41:58,510 --> 00:42:01,930
I won't use the notation of vector spaces.

1095
00:42:02,210 --> 00:42:05,550
I'll just use the complex conjugation.

1096
00:42:05,670 --> 00:42:07,430
So when thinking about vectors,

1097
00:42:07,670 --> 00:42:10,170
we complex conjugate them

1098
00:42:10,170 --> 00:42:12,390
by turning them from bras to kets.

1099
00:42:12,490 --> 00:42:14,510
When thinking of them as the coefficients,

1100
00:42:14,710 --> 00:42:16,410
just the numerical coefficients,

1101
00:42:16,630 --> 00:42:19,310
we'll use the notation of complex conjugation.

1102
00:42:19,310 --> 00:42:19,970
Star.

1103
00:42:22,030 --> 00:42:22,650
Alright,

1104
00:42:22,650 --> 00:42:23,530
so keep that in mind

1105
00:42:23,530 --> 00:42:26,230
that the dual vector space,

1106
00:42:27,150 --> 00:42:30,850
when you multiply a vector by a constant,

1107
00:42:31,070 --> 00:42:34,170
the image in the dual vector space

1108
00:42:34,170 --> 00:42:36,090
gets multiplied by the complex conjugate.

1109
00:42:37,310 --> 00:42:37,930
Otherwise,

1110
00:42:38,810 --> 00:42:39,430
well,

1111
00:42:39,430 --> 00:42:40,170
otherwise,

1112
00:42:41,230 --> 00:42:42,550
operations on the dual space

1113
00:42:42,550 --> 00:42:44,790
are similar to operations on the original space.

1114
00:42:45,050 --> 00:42:45,350
For example,

1115
00:42:45,570 --> 00:42:49,290
if a and b are two vectors,

1116
00:42:49,310 --> 00:42:51,330
and we add them,

1117
00:42:52,590 --> 00:42:53,290
then

1118
00:42:55,890 --> 00:42:56,930
the dual,

1119
00:42:57,110 --> 00:42:58,790
or the complex conjugate,

1120
00:42:59,150 --> 00:43:00,610
will just be the sums

1121
00:43:07,010 --> 00:43:10,210
of the dual vectors.

1122
00:43:11,910 --> 00:43:13,310
That's a lot of information,

1123
00:43:13,570 --> 00:43:15,110
and it pretty much allows you

1124
00:43:15,110 --> 00:43:19,290
to reconstruct the dual vector space.

1125
00:43:20,350 --> 00:43:21,330
As I said,

1126
00:43:21,330 --> 00:43:21,850
for example,

1127
00:43:21,950 --> 00:43:23,990
the dual vector space to the space of function,

1128
00:43:24,170 --> 00:43:24,270
yeah,

1129
00:43:24,270 --> 00:43:24,550
good.

1130
00:43:24,770 --> 00:43:26,430
Is there any significance

1131
00:43:26,430 --> 00:43:28,790
to putting the alpha star on the right?

1132
00:43:28,830 --> 00:43:29,130
Oh,

1133
00:43:31,810 --> 00:43:32,290
no,

1134
00:43:32,390 --> 00:43:33,970
there's no significance to it,

1135
00:43:33,970 --> 00:43:34,130
no.

1136
00:43:34,470 --> 00:43:34,950
Uh,

1137
00:43:35,810 --> 00:43:36,290
there's,

1138
00:43:36,290 --> 00:43:37,850
there's sort of a tradition

1139
00:43:37,850 --> 00:43:39,590
of keeping your formulas neat

1140
00:43:39,590 --> 00:43:41,470
by writing them a certain way,

1141
00:43:41,670 --> 00:43:42,650
but in this case,

1142
00:43:42,650 --> 00:43:42,930
no,

1143
00:43:43,030 --> 00:43:44,410
there is no significance to that.

1144
00:43:44,470 --> 00:43:45,150
That's a good question.

1145
00:43:45,390 --> 00:43:46,970
Other times there will be,

1146
00:43:47,030 --> 00:43:48,530
other objects there will be,

1147
00:43:48,530 --> 00:43:49,790
when we multiply operators,

1148
00:43:50,050 --> 00:43:51,970
when we multiply vectors by operators,

1149
00:43:52,790 --> 00:43:54,890
then it does matter where we put them.

1150
00:43:55,410 --> 00:43:56,410
But when it's just numbers,

1151
00:43:56,610 --> 00:43:56,810
no,

1152
00:43:56,810 --> 00:43:57,730
there's no significance.

1153
00:43:58,490 --> 00:43:58,950
Uh,

1154
